<TITLE> Police raid on JU finds few weapons </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jahangirnagar University, May 14 (bdnews24.com) A raid involving 300 policemen on six student halls of Jahangirnagar University only netted four sharp weapons--and a toy pistol. The raid in the early hours of Friday in the presence of the university's proctor Arzu Mia was criticised as a 'farce' by some students. The non-political students of the university claim that firearms have been used in almost all the clashes amongst the feuding groups of the pro-government Bangladesh Chhatra League in the last few months. The police said the raid was 'unannounced,' The proctor said the drive was a routine exercise to keep the situation under control and was not conducted on the basis of any specific information. Ashulia police chief Sirajul Islam said, "It was a part of our regular activities." Police said the toy pistol was found in the passageway of Bangabandhu Hall. Two machetes and some iron rods and pipes were also recovered from the hall. The law enforcers seized some blunt weapons from Mir Mosharraf Hossain Hall and Al Beruni Hall but found nothing noteworthy from the other three A number of BCL activists have sustained bullet injuries in intra-party clashes after the Awami League-led grand alliance government came to power. bdnews
